ikaaro 0.76.0 - 2017/01/18
==================================

  - Now we don't have to install itools to install itools,
    so installation with pip is easier
  - copy_handler method can take exclude_paterns parameter
  - Add microseconds to DateTime datatype
  - Update pygit2 requirements to 0.24.2
  - Update requirements.txt
  - Installation with pip is easier
  - Remove ABNF package (not used & no time to maintain)
  - Remove PML (no time to maintain)
  - Fix unit tests (clean tests if abort)
  - Add accept_cors in itools.web context
  - get_field: Add soft=True parameter (will be to False in future)
  - Add field name in resources fields
  - Add method to do requests on server (to simplify unit tests):

        server.do_request(method='GET', path='/', headers={}, body=None, context=None)

  - Fix bad context.status in some strange cases 299741377694b31e9d01fba63be144e347eebd0d
  - Server raise error on unsupported content type
  - ipkg-build support launching GULP (will be moved in ikaaro?)
  - html parser support html5
  - Improve error messages
  - Add "nl" translations
  - Views: Schema could be composed of fields or datatypes
  - CSV: Declare more mimetypes
  - Remove ipkg-build.py (now we always build on install)
  - Catalog: Allow to index decimal (as float)
  - Catalog: Improve performances
  - stl: Allow boolean and/or into stl:if
  - Core: better log errors on prototypes

Thanks to:

  - Florian Briand
  - Florent Chenebault
